claim: Haitian Creole is a linguistic structure spoken by 9.6 to 12 million humans.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Haitian Creole  (  -LSB- ˈheɪʃən_ˈkriːoʊl -RSB- -LSB- kreyòl ayisyen , links = no -RSB- , -LSB- kɣejɔl -RSB- ; créole haïtien  )  is a French-based creole language spoken by 9.6 -- 12million people worldwide , and the only language of most Haitians .
